<DOC><DOCNO> AP880708-0198 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-08-88 2107EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Reagan-Messages     07-08 0125</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Reagan-Messages,110</SECOND><HEAD>Reagan Sends Condolence Message to Nations With Iran Plane Victims</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Airliner Rdp Bjt</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan has sent messages ofcondolences to each of the countries that had citizens aboard theIran Air passenger plane that was shot down by a U.S. Navy warship,the State Department said Friday.   Deputy spokeswoman Phyllis Oakley said Reagan asked that hispersonal sympathy and condolences and those of the American peoplebe conveyed directly to the bereaved families.   The countries receiving the messages were Pakistan, the UnitedArab Emirates, Kuwait, India, Yugoslavia and Italy, she said.   On Sunday, shortly afte the plane was shot down, Reaganapologized to Iran for the incident and said that compensation forthe families is under consideration.</TEXT></DOC>